= Description
   Unicode methods for Ruby.

= Synopsis
   # Run with -Ku
   require 'fortress'
   
   λ { puts "hello" } => "Hello"
   ∑ [1,2,3]          => 6
   √ 49               => 7.0

= Author's Notes
	This library is named after the Fortress programming language, which is an
	offshoot of Fortran, created by Sun. Like Fortran is specializes in
	mathematical operations. Unlike Fortran, it fully supports Unicode
	operators.
	
	For more on Fortress, the programming language, please visit
	http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fortress_programming_language
	
= Author
   Daniel Berger